com.gh.bmd.jrt.routine

Class TemplateRoutine<INPUT,OUTPUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gh.bmd.jrt.routine.TemplateRoutine<INPUT,OUTPUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    INPUT - the input data type.
    OUTPUT - the output data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Routine<INPUT,OUTPUT>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractRoutine, TemplateRoutineBuilder

    public abstract class TemplateRoutine<INPUT,OUTPUT>
extends Object
implements Routine<INPUT,OUTPUT>
    Empty abstract implementation of a routine.

    This class is useful to avoid the need of implementing some of the methods defined in the interface.

    Created by davide on 10/17/14.

      • purge

        public void purge()
        Description copied from interface: Routine
        Makes the routine destroy all the cached invocation instances.

        This method is useful to force the release of external resources when done with the routine. Note however that the routine will still be usable after the method returns.

        Normally it is not needed to call this method.

        Specified by:
        purge in interface Routine<INPUT,OUTPUT>
